      public User()
      A blank constructor, useful for when we want to create our user object by manually parsing it from Firebase

    • User

      public User(String name, String email, String phoneNumber, String deviceID, String deviceToken)
      A constructor for the User object that contains the attributes that can be set as we create the user object
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the user
      email - The email of the user
      phoneNumber - The phone number of the user
      deviceID - The deviceID of the user
      deviceToken - The Firebase Messaging Service device token used to send notifications

    • User

      public User(String name, String email, String phoneNumber, String deviceID, String deviceToken, boolean optOutLotteryStatusNotifications, boolean optOutSpecificNotifications, boolean optOutAdminNotifications)
      A constructor for the User object that contains the attributes that can be set as we create the user object
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the user
      email - The email of the user
      phoneNumber - The phone number of the user
      deviceID - The deviceID of the user
      deviceToken - The Firebase Messaging Service device token used to send notifications
      optOutLotteryStatusNotifications - Whether user would like to receive lottery status notification or not
      optOutSpecificNotifications - Whether user would like to receive specific notification or not
      optOutAdminNotifications - Whether user would like to receive admin notification or not
